##### SUMMARY

Two peers are configured and they inherit from two different templates. The scripts alter routes received from peer 10.0.0.85 and push them to peer 10.0.99.4. The latter peer has rib-out enabled so that if it bounces the session the routes that had been previously advertised to it will be resent.
If the number of routes advertised to peer 10.0.99.4 is at 100K vpnv6 and 100K vpnv4 upon resetting peer 10.0.99.4 exabgp will make one attempt to reconnect and then will hang. The condition causes keepalives to stop going out from exabgp to the peers, such that after 90 seconds both peers are down and the exabgp logs are at that point completely quiet.

