}

void vs_test() {
        char szFileName[]="myfile.txt";
        PrintFError ("Error opening '%s'",szFileName);
}
```

Also a compiled binary is attached (elf arm 32 bit)

According to the following stackoverflow question:  
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37432797/snprintf-negative-zero-value-of-buffer-size

If you pass 0 on the size of the buffer the function shouldn't write to the buffer and so it can also be NULL.

The current implementation call memory.store either way and so when I set hook on mem_write the hook being called although no write should be happening.

It caused in: 
https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/libc/vsnprintf.py
and 
https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/libc/snprintf.py

I will make a pull request fixing this issue.

