When I was working with the OpenThread code recently, I've encountered a problem with failing thread-cert tests, so I did an experiment with seed generation in posix RNG:

```
void posixRandomInit(void)
{
    time_t now;
    time(&now);
    s_state = (uint32_t)now + NODE_ID;
}
```

After applying this change, some of the tests started to fail at random. Here's an example result:
https://travis-ci.org/NordicSemiconductor/openthread/builds/163050301

I think it might be worth to pull this change and fix failing tests, to minimize the possibility that future PRs will face problems with tests themselves. I can attempt to fix the test and submit the PR if you want.

